To upscale, just leave the prompt like it is.

If you get weird results, maybe change the prompt.
As example:
While upscaling a marble face with this prompt, the marble face gets a human face.

To get marble, just add marble in the front.

Controlpanel:
Use the Upscale "Yes/No" to apply the whole Upscale process.
Turn it off if you want to prepare your image before upscaling.

To disable the background fix, just set it on "No"

Choose here your Checkpoint and LoRAs.
But keep the LCM LoRA!

Denoise 0.05-0.10/0.15 is a normal upscale.
Higher Denoise = More Creativity

0.20-0.25 works also fine but with more creativity

a robot with a large body and a large body, with a large body and a large, white body

If you get an error, it could be that your image is to small.
Set Tile then to: 512

After that put it back to 1024.
